21 convention of a political party), and an equal amount for each general
22 election.
23 (3) For the office of state senator or, member of the state board of
24 education or a candidate for local office whose jurisdiction has a
25 population that is 50,000 or more, $1,000 $2,000 for each primary election
26 (, or in lieu thereof, a caucus or convention of a political party), and an
27 equal amount for each general election.
28 (b) For the purposes of this section, the face value of a loan at the end
29 of the period of time allocable to the primary or general election is the
30 amount subject to the limitations of this section. A loan in excess of the
31 limits herein provided may be made during the allocable period if such
32 loan is reduced to the permissible level, when combined with all other
33 contributions from the person making such loan, at the end of such
34 allocable period.
35 (c) For the purposes of this section, all contributions made by
36 unemancipated children under 18 years of age shall be considered to be

